The paper deals with the problem of dynamic approximate membership, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper discusses a variant of this problem where the size of the set is not known in advance, which is a natural and important extension of the problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the trade-off between space complexity and accuracy, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper presents lower bounds and matching upper bounds, which is a common approach in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC, and cs.DM are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
